notes.backstory:
He's coming to ten towns to investigate Crenshinibon and the substance called chardalyn. There is a purported link between the two.&nbsp; He's working on a series of monographs about Crenshinibon and has traced it's path from the far southern deserts to the far north of Icewind Dale. Now he's travelled to the Dale to gather more information.&nbsp;


Geki is of a merchant family so he's travelled quite extensively in the area around Waterdeep and the Sword Coast, but this is his first trip on his own and with no mercantile purpose. The letter of introduction from his masters at the Watchful Order of Magists and another from his parent's mercantile guild (Sword Mountain Mercantile Guild) have stood in good stead to get him this far in his travels, but the road ends here in Ten Towns.


He hopes to make friends with others that he's heard called adventurers, like the tales of the teachers at the Watchful Order, but is wary as some of them seem unreliable at best. Choosing solid companions&nbsp;when facing danger seems a good way to stay alive. He wants to make good choices and recruit some to travel with him if such is needed and he's almost certain it will.
